TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimal Consumption Policy under Uncertain Income
AU  - Mendelson, Haim
AU  - Amihud, Yakov
Y1  - 1982/06/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.28.6.683
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.28.6.683
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 683
EP  - 697
VL  - 28
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper considers the consumption behavior of a risk-averse consumer with a preference for immediate consumption who faces an uncertain income stream and plans for a finite or infinite number of periods. The consumer may borrow up to a limit or save, where both saving and borrowing are subject to the same positive rate of interest. We derive the optimal consumption policies for both finite and infinite planning horizons, investigate their characteristics, and analyze their economic and behavioral implications.
AB  - This paper considers the consumption behavior of a risk-averse consumer with a preference for immediate consumption who faces an uncertain income stream and plans for a finite or infinite number of periods. The consumer may borrow up to a limit or save, where both saving and borrowing are subject to the same positive rate of interest. We derive the optimal consumption policies for both finite and infinite planning horizons, investigate their characteristics, and analyze their economic and behavioral implications.
